transcript.text: Start by uploading your photo into the Designer Studio.

Once your photo is uploaded, you can transform its style by exploring a variety of effects available in the mask and border section or applying artistic filters that can give your photo a unique flair.
Additionally, you can enhance the visuals by adjusting settings such as brightness, contrast, saturation, and hue to achieve the perfect look.
Next, let's make some specific adjustments to the uploaded photo.
Begin by cropping the image to focus on the desired area.
This can be done by simply adjusting the cropping frame to include only the parts of the image you want to keep.
After cropping, you can remove the background to isolate the main subject of the photo.
This step helps in making the subject stand out more prominently.
To make the photo even more realistic, you can change the background using the Position and Layer options.
These options allow you to place your subject in a new setting, giving the photo a completely different context and feel.
If you want to add one of your own photos as the background of the page, you can control the opacity to blend it seamlessly with the foreground.
Once you have the desired effect, click on Set Background from the toolbar to finalize the changes.
With these features, you can create stunning and personalized images that truly stand out.
